{"name":"BX Options Class Builder Classes","pages":[{"name":"Archon","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 32\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum WIS 9</p><p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: WIS and CHA</p><p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p><p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 10</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Any, including shields</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common, Beast, Elemental, Elf, Fey</span></p><p>Archons are high elf servants of the primal powers—elementals, beast lords, and demiurges—who first bestowed wisdom upon the elven race. Archons do not worship these beings, but instead honour ancient pacts of mutual assistance and protection, from which an archon’s arcane power stems.</p><h3>Abilities</h3><p> @UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.GmqbYyr7wpzHKsFY]{Arcane Magic}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.PQbLkH7c6uf0Eamh]{Arcane Pacts}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.4RKmyqpy4jMYNoWR]{Encounter Bonus}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.0oB159Mg3ZXjxCcj]{Infravision}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.33MwByrgldMHxbVT]{Saving Throw Bonus}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.ldtuVwcaPP6i6v70]{After Reaching 10th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/ArchonProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></div></div></div></div>","markdown":""},"_id":"isDjy7b1iFRY1XOV","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.JqmOQ4e2JwUkLvIV.JournalEntryPage.isDjy7b1iFRY1XOV"}}},{"name":"Assassin","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 62\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: None</p><p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: DEX</p><p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p><p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p><p><strong>Armour</strong>: Leather, no shields</p><p><strong>Weapons:</strong> Any except two-handed <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">melee weapons</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">Assassins are humans trained to murder efficiently. They use stealth and deception to get close to targets so they can deliver a quick, killing blow with either a melee weapon or well- placed shot with a missile. Their specialised skills are not well-suited for dungeon crawls or wilderness exploration, but assassins do thrive in urban environments where they may be hired as “equalisers” in matters of political intrigue, turf wars, and commercial subterfuge.</span></p><p>Abilities:</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.ZsDy5hRBwkS2pTtb]{Assassinate}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.tOI3qzHJ612scm5d]{Climb sheer surfaces (CS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.KCEjV8nOHJERzB3B]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.lwAuJRpw3w3osJU1]{Disguise}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.HyVp7wC8PGj0BTv4]{Hear noise (HN)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.0vObOfUNdDV02iP8]{Hide In Shadows (HS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.pmL9XrlTW0EeueXz]{Move silently (MS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.7ulgWOduOl87mWzK]{Poison}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.cYOMszyzZBqe1ETC]{Restrictions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.XdJDgivIEacFujyu]{Thief Skills}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.DrRn7sm8zvFpQD41]{After Reaching 9th Level}</p></div></div></div></div><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/AssassinProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"551\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"Urs59aAIb4slpUBD","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.uu7VP2BEISmhUWyP.JournalEntryPage.Urs59aAIb4slpUBD"}}},{"name":"Barbarian","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 38\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum DEX 9, maximum WIS 15</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: STR</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d10</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Any non-plate, including shields (see below)</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any (see below)</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Common, Tribal tongue</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">Barbarians are stout humans who form tribal societies in a specific “home” terrain (q.v., Appendix F). They live by foraging, hunting, herding, and basic farming, yet have intricate clan hierarchies, laws, customs, and social taboos. Devoted to nature worship, they view divine magic as proof of the primordial gods’ favour, but arcane magic is anathema. Barbarians do not like cities and do not welcome outsiders.</span></p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.f4kPmn7ZJEF54nTI]{Climb sheer surfaces (CS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.V8uC3gIeht3ozxjc]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.p9DBr5sPavk77cXd]{Dodge}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.mseCUfGs6B0ZBf9M]{Hear noise (HN)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.9OAndGRQ0Ny87zJg]{Hide (HD)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.9x4C1jOCLK39LXo8]{Hide In Shadows (HS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.9OAndGRQ0Ny87zJg]{Hide (HD)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.9x4C1jOCLK39LXo8]{Hide In Shadows (HS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.o12QB5hzS46Qh3Cg]{Move silently (MS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.Z3lLxMSPdPBYTcGY]{Superstitious}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.jjSKGWXdm0b7tVD7]{Wild}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.5xUw2VP4YxL5t8qs]{Wilderness Survival}</p><h3>Progression</h3></div></div></div></div><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/BarbarianProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"548\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"tFu7UcMEUfmXkvbp","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.SVxgxJmnq6A95bGZ.JournalEntryPage.tFu7UcMEUfmXkvbp"}}},{"name":"Bard","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Requirements</strong>: Minimum DEX 9, minimum WIS 9</span></p><div title=\"Page 64\"><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: CHA</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d4</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Leather, no shields Weapons: Any one-handed melee or missile weapons</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common, +2 additional</span></p><p>Bards are human warrior-poets who chronicle the exploits of daring adventures as participants. They relate these histories through song and verse, which are lent credibility as eyewitnesses to the events described in their epics. Between adventures, bards earn a living by entertaining others with tales of adventure—in fact, adventuring parties sometimes hire bards to enhance their heroic reputations (perhaps, it is imagined, with a liberal application of flattering embellishment).</p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.1IO9kPfTKDGMbOQj]{Bardic Songs}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.GhIyJn6syq0gSV5R]{Climb sheer surfaces (CS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.BEmhdGkOLsjacjCX]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.gMQaoxMXWRi2doeT]{Enchantment}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.Gn480omzRNEd3lQC]{Hear noise (HN)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.JSAPOfBpcVOIixVI]{Lore}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.uV1z2LDBuH7abgQ1]{Move silently (MS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.UBls7IcOEFhB0AmL]{Open Locks (OL)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.SYb31lMVQ0RkCrgK]{Pick Pockets (PP)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.gMR0BrbcyjqClrlG]{Read Languages}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.UUfGUDPYW6obkhnc]{Restrictions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.bSnDhlk5J6k36E6p]{Thief Skills}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.ru8DrZdrrMPBcBI5]{Use Magic Item}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.RC2BTz6KzZFilRGO]{After Reaching 9th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3></div><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/BardProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"550\" /><p> </p>","markdown":""},"_id":"4jOkh0SUZqT1K4ml","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.bgH1jMrKrxvX51SL.JournalEntryPage.4jOkh0SUZqT1K4ml"}}},{"name":"Beast-talker","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 40\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum DEX 9, minimum STR 13</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: WIS</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Leather, no shields</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any (see below)</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</span></p><p>Beast-talkers are humans raised in animal totem or zoolatry-based societies, or perhaps even by animals themselves. At home in the wilds, beast-talkers create a sanctuary for beasts to live in safety, away from settled areas. As implied, they can communicate with animals, who perceive beast-talkers as animals themselves; within their home range, beast-talkers are recognized as alphas by all but the most aggressive and territorial beasts.</p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.GXLemZaZXbmgXawa]{Animal Companion}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.eiVqxElnZRogYb6P]{Call of the Wild}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.uIbme96g3IvnvhqC]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.1rlPi6W97QXeEJ1E]{Home Range}</p></div></div></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.rO52QRXjiXBzz0gO]{Restrictions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.0BGpXGHBUm6zJZoS]{After Reaching 9th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/Beast-TalkerProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"559\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"apWFPloyQgLdzhEp","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.dVm9fhiHP4AHmvQ8.JournalEntryPage.apWFPloyQgLdzhEp"}}},{"name":"Berserker","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 42\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: None</p><p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: STR</p><p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d8</p><p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p><p><strong>Armour</strong>: Leather or furs, including <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">shields</span></p><p><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any, except missiles (see class abilities<span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">)</span></p><p><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</p><p>Berserkers are human fighters dedicated to an animal totem or beast cult. Berserker “clans” model themselves along the social habits and hierarchies of their totem animal. In clan or tribal cultures, berserkers may mimic their animal’s behaviour, sleep cycles, diet, and living conditions to form a more intimate bond with the beast’s spirit; in more “advanced” societies, berserkers may observe such traits only symbolically.</p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.N2U5jdMXdRqqSzHj]{Alignment}</p></div></div></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.3BZ3CyJQ5Ka7Xs6H]{Animal Totems}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.4eXK0y3YqcgM5OEJ]{Berserk}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.3xiz8uQq5THTqYhI]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.tnIpaZQLMSoHM1hh]{After Reaching 9th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/BerserkerProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"551\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"L5fqelvMIXsaW69b","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.wY0pmrYRHOarB46w.JournalEntryPage.L5fqelvMIXsaW69b"}}},{"name":"Crusader","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 18\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum STR 9</p><p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: WIS</p><p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p><p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Any, including shields</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any permitted by their order</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">A cleric sub-class, crusaders are human warrior-priests of religious fighting orders. Such orders are auxiliary and subordinate to their parent church or sect, whose mission they support through force of arms. Common to all orders is an “infidel,” or the primary target of its martial attention, which could be as specific as a pagan tribe or rival sect, or as broad as beings of an opposing race, nation, or alignment. Not all churches support fighting orders, nor are all orders truly subordinate.</span></p><p>N.B. As self-righteous fighters with limited clerical ability, crusaders are a good template for paladin (or anti-paladin) archetypes in settings where the struggle between good and evil is foundational and epic. In settings where alignment struggles are not the focus of conflict—where the line between good and evil is blurred and subjective—crusaders can occupy a more multifaceted niche if referees exploit each fighting order’s history, mission, and bias to create moral grey areas.</p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.JXsSHOwgpp11Y0Ql]{Combat}</p></div></div></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.vWWnfN1SrMf8IJJ3]{Conviction}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.rJQMMlFDqGiN9K0w]{Divine Magic}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.SWjDXJ50otgBkI75]{Foe Sense}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.hF1t3VgSKl42tkb5]{Weakness}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.lTH1JPWSuX6xKW8m]{After Reaching 9th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/CrusaderProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"556\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"F0NMfI0rHtwSzIo1","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.cEIPOcY6gF3SIL3c.JournalEntryPage.F0NMfI0rHtwSzIo1"}}},{"name":"Elder","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p> </p><div title=\"Page 26\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum CON 9, minimum WIS 9</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: WIS</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 12</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Any, including shields Weapons: Any permitted by their deity (see below)</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common, Dwarfish, Gnome, Goblin, Kobold</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">Elders are dwarf clerics, dedicated to dwarven immortal powers. Elders renounce their home clan when they take up the faith, joining a clerical clan dedicated either to an individual deity or (in smaller settlements) the entire dwarf pantheon.</span></p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.hqoXcm8WVfUGo27e]{Combat}</p></div></div></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.mUAr199xzyWrdKbq]{Detect Construction Tricks}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.vnTcHeBw92Td2Ocy]{Detect Room Traps}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.5BU9J8QmywhEGE8e]{Divine Magic}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.BKBILEeikWkdnB8V]{Divine Power}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.njZrNWj7RwMmQKtg]{Infravision}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.YtaA5O7ZhZwm6bbW]{Listening at doors.}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.AVyyI0Obpi2anJyf]{After Reaching 10th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/ElderProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"496\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"1dCpV5NN8PZBI3dy","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.fkghDiMLVdaTgVsh.JournalEntryPage.1dCpV5NN8PZBI3dy"}}},{"name":"Necromancer","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 54\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Maximum CHA 12</p><p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: INT</p><p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d4</p><p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: None</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: Dagger only Languages: Alignment, Common</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">Necromancers are human magic-users fascinated with the cycle of life and death, studying the positive and negative energies associated with each to re-animate the dead or create life anew. Not surprisingly, their scholarship is perceived as unnatural, and they are shunned and mistrusted as a result.</span></p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.sIyhEFClqUjDe3Zd]{Arcane Magic}</p></div></div></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.MHHomPq4NxKxhSIa]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.QQs03Fvsp0mLVRdG]{Control Golems}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.eCRdZrSfN5mb1jcm]{Create Golems}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.P1qISIlpVd8WUCz6]{Drain Vitality}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.LRLunUXYfYzJKLuM]{Restrictions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.pFNSh55sL0vJwe2G]{Turn Undead}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.4T8dqxzGtRvCFno4]{After Reaching 11th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/NecromancerProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"552\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"ZUDmdkEkTrsVZB6V","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.R5YB5qByKLLVPUuW.JournalEntryPage.ZUDmdkEkTrsVZB6V"}}},{"name":"Scout","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 66\"><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum STR 9</p><p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: DEX</p><p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p><p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Any non-plate, no shields</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any except two-handed melee weapons</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</span></p><p>Scouts are humans who’ve adapted to life in the wilderness, working to keep stretches of untamed territory safe for travelers and local populations. Scouts know their territory well—both its terrain and its denizens—warding it against foes that might pose a danger to local settlements. They believe that birds, beasts, and plants have as much a right to life as “civilised” peoples and try to ensure the peace and safety of all—they’re just as likely to run down poachers as to guide peaceful travelers safely through a dark forest.</p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.OBNv9aZCZN88Ztrp]{Climb sheer surfaces (CS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.qVzxi0dFOGgq8hmP]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.gUazWQAJ7kBosrYD]{Familiar Territory}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.BmkVRSjzLinLAbuQ]{Hear noise (HN)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.Vo3ewNVyW4uCLQBR]{Hide In Shadows (HS)}</p></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.PaV9Wp7KWpDeLFim]{Infravision}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.3Weu7PL8KHxxMmli]{Move silently (MS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.DXQxcHSt9mGwetDe]{Restrictions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.cox3el4IX4XcugtH]{Scouting Missions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.Oiz7S6iB3nwkyZzL]{Surprise}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.ifgJD1A3dzL9YRnJ]{Thief Skills}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.YcQQnFEj2kNU00fV]{Use Magic Items}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.EDEwGa3WogsH8g5J]{Wilderness Survival}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.cEKG2kqFG30ogyeS]{After Reaching 9th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/ScoutProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"555\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"RahcTymB9vagfok9","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.oxx9y9W5flHDMKCW.JournalEntryPage.RahcTymB9vagfok9"}}},{"name":"Shaman","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 20\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum CON 9</p><p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: WIS</p><p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p><p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Leather, no shields</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any one-handed melee</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">A shaman is a tribal cleric common to barbarian and nomadic cultures. They revere animal spirits as exemplars of proper outlook and conduct in all matters.</span></p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.058hAbZaTCwI6N25]{Animal Spirit Guides}</p></div></div></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.RuFFMtw3oQcy7J25]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.tLtDLBnl48tG89zr]{Detect Hidden Doors}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.l5Ac1PxicgeW3xa4]{Detect Hidden Objects}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.a42teoirHrnGhvZA]{Divine Magic}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.uwrm7O9oO82EyuiE]{Hear noise (HN)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.rJ4PaDH6KbzreFgQ]{Shape Change}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.tzZw3Rzyj0kKW9ta]{Speak with Animals}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.JSUrNbwkgwqpmZqp]{After Reaching 9th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/ShamanProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"553\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"sx1dzmYX65YQ6hNF","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.EozCgjZEkiOz69CM.JournalEntryPage.sx1dzmYX65YQ6hNF"}}},{"name":"Sorcerer","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 56\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum CHA 9</p><p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: INT</p><p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d4</p><p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: None</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: Dagger only</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">Sorcerers are human magic-users who derive their spell casting ability from pacts with one or more powerful extra-planar patrons.</span></p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.FaweyrVzc8joDrCc]{Arcane Magic}</p></div></div></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.4Mh1NrO4LagGZquw]{Combat}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.6jRI98s9ZcO0MHan]{Patron Reactions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.czLLMJdrGyi3G41F]{Restrictions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.YeaWJm2lhhpn0LeN]{After Reaching 11th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/SorcererProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"557\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"oe6wr6LuPYlAxQoo","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.qsEfjZXOTNttMURY.JournalEntryPage.oe6wr6LuPYlAxQoo"}}},{"name":"Warden","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 48\"><div><div><div><p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum CON 9, minimum DEX 9</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: DEX and STR</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 8</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: Any appropriate to size, including shields</span></p><p><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any appropriate to size <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">(see Combat ability)</span></p><p><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common, <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">Halfling</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary)\">These halfling “outdoorsmen” patrol the wilderness surrounding a halfling community against threats and mis- chief. Wardens work at the pleasure of the local sheriff and thus share responsibility for the community’s safety and defense.</span></p><h3>Abilities</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.XkcJhYcSd8YDezAx]{Combat}</p></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.SdfhT6M2Q7fmDI7h]{Defensive Bonus}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.CHznKFnaDqiMgqdW]{Detect Room Traps}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.ePq06nGenSXp0cYW]{Encounter Bonus}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.8YTAY5KsAr1YThBL]{Hear noise (HN)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.nrflE4IxGgN2gb9m]{Hiding}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.LMEhXHfFD8NgEX7l]{Move silently (MS)}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.D8ZKglxUqJ1sdH2b]{Restrictions}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.y8gBVVhE2KW7YmYj]{Special Foes by Terrain}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.h1VO27tHMdubHGoy]{Wilderness Survival}</p></div></div><p>@UUID[Compendium.bx-options.BXO Abilities.qbMy6Q0ke0QmucRd]{After Reaching 4th Level}</p><h3>Progression</h3><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/WardenProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"393\" />","markdown":""},"_id":"X7nnKBhvqr9OgZIE","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.LUeCA9Zkdn4Xyy6X.JournalEntryPage.X7nnKBhvqr9OgZIE"}}},{"sort":-100000,"name":"BX OPTIONS CREDITS","type":"text","_id":"92CbbbNhxg0pyvYx","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Firstly, all thanks should go to Erin D. Smale who remains an asset to the OSR community. I encourage you to purchase this book, as the classes listed here only scratch the surface of what this incredible book does in explaining creating your own classes for BX D&amp;D and Old-School Essentials.</p><p>If you'd like to support this author, take a look at his work:</p><p>https://welshpiper.com/packages/bx-options-class-builder/</p><p>Enjoy!</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"name":"Appendix G","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Page 75\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Beast-talkers and shamans bond with animals as companions or spirit guides, respectively, from whom they receive aspects of the animal’s power.</p>\n<p>Animals from the <em>Old-School Essentials Rules Tome </em>and their suggested special abilities are shown below. For referees who wish to expand this list, consider “animal” to be any non-intelligent, higher-order bird or beast native to the set- ting. This classification may, at the referee’s option, include fish, aquatic mam- mals, and assorted arthropods or annelids, but never plasmodial or amoeboid creatures (slimes, moulds, puddings, oozes, or fungi).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/AnimalSpecialAbilitiesG.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"655\" /></p>"},"_id":"tEmE2cWundzXDIMg","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.bx-options.BXO Progressions.6jacsjz142T2Ar40.JournalEntryPage.tEmE2cWundzXDIMg"}}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"TmxwZSjVycovamI9":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.zbd8dmLJHvaEgk7e"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"ose","systemVersion":"1.6.8","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1667772691490,"modifiedTime":1667777765464,"lastModifiedBy":"TmxwZSjVycovamI9"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"tZ2nPQr4iQbsaCo8"}
